# AITBC v0.5.0 Release Plan — Bridge to Production

## Overview

v0.5.0 completes the deferred work from v0.4.26 and bridges the codebase toward v1.0.0 mainnet readiness. This is the **last feature release before v1.0.0** — after v0.5.0, only mainnet integration and security audit remain.

**Target Date**: Q1 2025
**Theme**: "Finish the Foundation"
**Success Criteria**: All v0.4.26 deferred items resolved; codebase passes internal security review.

---

## P0: Complete JWT Auth Migration (Agent A)

### Problem
6 high-risk routers still use API key auth. These must be migrated before API keys can be removed entirely.

### Remaining Routers

| Router | Current Auth | Target | Status |
|--------|-------------|--------|--------|
| `routers/admin.py` | `require_admin_key()` | `AdminDep` | 🔴 Not started |
| `routers/cache_management.py` | `require_admin_key()` | `AdminDep` | 🔴 Not started |
| `routers/marketplace_enhanced.py` | `require_admin_key()` | `AdminDep` | 🔴 Not started |
| `routers/marketplace_enhanced_simple.py` | `require_admin_key()` | `AdminDep` | 🔴 Not started |
| `contexts/payments/routers/payments.py` | `require_admin_key()` | `AdminDep` | 🔴 Not started |
| `contexts/security/routers/security_router.py` | `require_admin_key()` | `AdminDep` | 🔴 Not started |

### Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] All 6 routers migrated to JWT dependencies
- [ ] No `from ..deps import require_*` in any router
- [ ] All routes compile and tests pass

