## P0: DB/Redis Backing for Mock State

### Problem
Mock routers still use module-global `dict()` for state. This was deferred in v0.4.26. Production requires persistent state.

### Affected Routers

| Router | State Type | Replacement |
|--------|-----------|-------------|
| `routers/swarm.py` | `dict` of swarm configs | Redis hash |
| `routers/training.py` | `dict` of training jobs | Redis sorted set |
| `routers/hermes.py` | `dict` of message queues | Redis streams |
| `contexts/marketplace/services/marketplace_service.py` | In-memory offer cache | Redis cache |

### Work Required

| Task | Status | Owner |
|------|--------|-------|
| Audit all mock routers for `dict()` state | 🔴 Not started | Agent A |
| Add Redis models for swarm/training/hermes state | 🔴 Not started | TBD |
| Add cache invalidation on state mutation | 🔴 Not started | TBD |
| Ensure `debug=false` disables mock state creation | 🟡 Partial | Agent B |

### Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] No module-global `dict()` for persistent state
- [ ] State survives service restart
- [ ] Multiple coordinator instances share state via Redis

---

## P1: Systemd Hardening

### Problem
Systemd units were deferred in v0.4.26. Production services need security isolation.

### Work Required

| Task | Status | Owner |
|------|--------|-------|
| Audit all `.service` files in `systemd/` | 🔴 Not started | Agent B |
| Add `PrivateTmp=yes` to all services | 🔴 Not started | Agent B |
| Add `NoNewPrivileges=yes` to all services | 🔴 Not started | Agent B |
| Add `ProtectSystem=strict` to all services | 🔴 Not started | Agent B |
| Add `ProtectHome=yes` to all services | 🔴 Not started | Agent B |
| Move secrets to `/etc/aitbc/%N.env` | 🔴 Not started | Agent B |
| Add `WatchdogSec=30` + `NotifyAccess=all` | 🔴 Not started | Agent B |
| Add `Restart=on-failure`, `RestartSec=5` | 🔴 Not started | Agent B |
| Create `aitbc` user (non-root) for all services | 🔴 Not started | DevOps |

### Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] `systemd-analyze security` shows no "unsafe" services
- [ ] No secrets in `/etc/systemd/system/*.service`
- [ ] All services run as `aitbc` user
- [ ] Services auto-restart on crash

